A message type enumeration, corresponding to the messages described in Appendix A1 of Lamport's "Part-time Parliament" with the following two exceptions: The NEW message is used to ask a parliament member to initiate a new decree. It's not a message that's part of the consensus protocol. The NULL message type is used in many response messages (since response is not a part of the protocol) to indicate that no non-trivial information is being conveyed, but is sent in order to conform to the IPC client/server request/response API.
